docs.snippet: The members of St. Andrews Society, who have put bread into the mouths of many Scotch widows and orphans, celebrated the 104th Anniversary of the Association, last evening, by dining together at the St. Nicholas Hotel.

headline.main: ST. ANDREW'S SOCIETY.; ANNIVERSARY DINNER AT THE ST. NICHOLAS. Speeches by Mr. Adam Norrie, Wm. M. Evarts, Esq., E.M. Archibald, H.B.M. Consul, Hon. John J. Crittenden, and others.

docs.lead_paragraph: The members of St. Andrews Society, who have put bread into the mouths of many Scotch widows and orphans, celebrated the 104th Anniversary of the Association, last evening, by dining together at the St. Nicholas Hotel.
